  "narrative_arc": "Family of four living in a semi-basement apartment that floods when it rains. Bong documents the vertical architecture of class — the Kims below ground, the Parks above, and the secret man hidden in the sub-basement. Each family occupies a different altitude in the same city, and water flows downhill.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "The Kim family dome maps class as architecture. Layer 5 (Housing) is literally underground. Layer 9 (Environment) shows how infrastructure failure (flooding) targets the lowest residents. Their dome vs. the Park family dome is the same city measured at different altitudes.",
